'''Usa Clan''' (宇佐氏) is a Japanese {{ill|clan|ja|氏族|12=draft|12=draft}}. In ancient times, the clan served as {{ill|Usa Kuni no miyatsuko|ja|宇佐国造|12=draft|12=draft}} and Usa {{ill|Hyotoku|ja|評督|12=draft|12=draft}}, later prospering as the shrine family of {{ill|Usa Jingū|ja|宇佐八幡宮|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Overview ==
The Usa clan traces its lineage back to {{ill|Usatsuhiko no Mikoto|ja|菟狭津彦命|12=draft|12=draft}}, a figure mentioned in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|記紀|12=draft|12=draft}}, as the ancestral founder and hereditary {{ill|Usa Kuni no miyatsuko|ja|宇佐国造|12=draft|12=draft}}. Usatsuhiko no Mikoto was said to be the son of {{ill|Amenokushimori no Mikoto|ja|天三降命|12=draft|12=draft}}, a descendant of {{ill|Takami Musubi no Mikoto|ja|高皇産霊尊|12=draft|12=draft}}, as detailed in the {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft|12=draft}}.

During the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, when the imperial court extended influence over the worship of Hachiman, a shrine administrator was appointed to {{ill|Usa Jingū|ja|宇佐八幡宮|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="A">『戦国人名事典 コンパクト版』, pp. 141-142</ref> Initially, the {{ill|Miwa clan|ja|大神氏|12=draft|12=draft}} held the position of Great Shrine Administrator (Ōmiya no Sakan), while the {{ill|Karashima Clan|ja|辛嶋氏|12=draft|12=draft}}, a clan of immigrant origin, oversaw rituals. However, during the {{ill|Dōkyō Incident|ja|宇佐八幡宮神託事件|12=draft|12=draft}}, Usa Ikemori assumed the Great Shrine Administrator role when the position became vacant.<ref name="D">『八幡宮創祀のlocationについて』</ref>

Until the Nara period, the site was primarily dedicated to Hachiman worship, unrelated to the Usa clan’s original faith in the deity {{ill|Himegami|ja|比咩神|12=draft|12=draft}}. The clan’s association with Hachiman only began in limited periods between 755 and 773, during the {{ill|Tempyo Shoho|ja|天平勝宝|12=draft|12=draft}} era. According to the oldest records, such as the {{ill|Hachiman Usa Shrine Oracle Collection|ja|八幡宇佐宮御託宣集|12=draft|12=draft}}, Himegami was originally enshrined on a mountain later occupied by Hachiman.<ref name="D"/>

During the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, the Ōgami clan held the role of Great Shrine Administrator, while the Usa clan served as Lesser Shrine Administrators. However, after the founding of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachiman Shrine|ja|石清水八幡宮|12=draft|12=draft}}, the Usa clan took advantage of the vacancy to become Shrine Administrators.<ref name="A"/><ref>八幡宇佐宮御託宣集</ref>

By the late Heian period, figures like {{ill|Usa Kinnori|ja|宇佐公則|12=draft|12=draft}} emerged, extending the clan’s influence across {{ill|Kyushu|ja|九州|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="A"/> Usa Kimichi married a daughter of {{ill|Taira no Kiyomori|ja|Taira no Kiyomori|12=draft|12=draft}}, hosting the exiled Emperor Antoku in his residence during the {{ill|Battle of Dan-no-ura|ja|壇ノ浦|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="A"/> During the {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, the clan retained control of Usa Hachiman Shrine.

Throughout the {{ill|Sengoku period|ja|戦国時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, the Usa clan served lords like the {{ill|Ōuchi clan|ja|大内氏|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Ōtomo Clan|ja|大友氏|12=draft|12=draft}}. However, their military role diminished, and events like the burning of Usa Shrine led to the clan’s displacement.<ref name="A"/>

After the {{ill|Kuroda Clan|ja|黒田氏|12=draft|12=draft}} took control of Buzen Province, Usa Kōri’s descendants, such as Miyase Kōki, transitioned into vassals of {{ill|Kuroda Nagamasa|ja|黒田長政|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="A"/>

